From f66bd96dfe89a813e2d047b87dbac36ede86753a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lucas <lucas@eliteaero.com.br>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 01:12:32 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] [Bugfix][Quantization] GGUF: cache canonical shard order
 on param to avoid per-forward sorting

Move _canonical_shard_order into GGUFLinearMethod as a @staticmethod.
Compute the canonical order once in _create_padded_weight_param and store
it as canonical_shard_id on the padded parameter via set_weight_attrs.
The apply() path reads that cached list directly instead of re-sorting
shard_id on every forward pass.

Fix the QKV assert message to name the valid set explicitly.
Extend the test to assert canonical_shard_id is set on the param.

Signed-off-by: Lucas <lucas@eliteaero.com.br>
